value.value: Masa mamaria hipoecoica
A breast mass visualized by sonography that displays a lower than normal echo signal (and this that appears dark gray in the typical ultrasound image).

definition.value: Ultrasonography (US) is an essential tool for evaluating breast masses. Irregular hypoechoic masses on breast ultrasound are usually considered suspicious lesions.

value.value: Quiste ovárico unilocular
An ovarian cyst without septa and a solid component.
Torsión mesentérica

definition.value: Mesenteric torsion is a pathological rotation of the intestinal tract around the axis of the mesenteric root, resulting in rapid occlusion of the cranial mesenteric artery.

value.value: Ruidos intestinales agudos
Abnormal bowel sounds of an unually high frequency.

definition.value: This finding is characteristic of Ogilvie syndrome.

value.value: Exacerbado por medicamentos opiáceos

definition.value: Applied to a sign orr symptom that is worsed by administration of opiate medications.
Opiate drugs increase pain in narcotic bowel syndrome.

value.value: Granuloma mamario
Formation of a non-necrotizing granuloma in breat tissue typically in combination with a localized infiltrate of multi-nucleated giant cells, epithelioid histiocytes, lymphocytes, and plasma cells.
Exposición a fragancias cosméticas

definition.value: A history of exposure to fragrances found in cosmetic products.

value.value: Sudoración y enrojecimiento en el área preauricular en respuesta a la masticación.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Sweating and flushing in the preauricular area in response to mastication

label.value: Sweating and flushing in the preauricular area in response to mastication

value.value: Sweating and flushing in the preauricular area in response to mastication or a salivary stimulus. Facial warmth, flushing, and sweating in the territory of the auriculotemporal nerve overlying the parotid gland, which may include the preauricular skin, the temporal skin, the scalp, and the temporomandibular joint region. Symptoms occur during meals, especially with spicy and sour foods. This feature is inferred to be a consequence of injury to the auriculotemporal nerve, a branch if the trigeminal nerve.
Disminución de la actividad de la glioxilato reductasa hepática
Activity of glyoxylate reductase/hydroxypyruvate reductase (GRHPR; EC 1.1.1.79) in liver below the lower limit of normal.
Vacuolización de linfocitos PAS positivos
Presence of lymphocytes with positive staining for periodic acid-Schiff (PAS) cytoplasmic vacuoles.

definition.value: Pompe disease (glycogen storage disease type II, acid maltase deficiency) is an inherited metabolic disorder in which a deficiency of the lysosomal enzyme acid alpha-glucosidase (EC 3.2.1.3/20) causes glycogen storage. Vacuolated lymphocytes - in essence, lysosomes filled with nondegraded material occur in many storage disorders. Glycogen storage in Pompe disease is found in lysosomes throughout the body, including lymphocytes in peripheral blood, liver, and skin.

value.value: Macrófagos de la médula ósea cargados de lípidos

definition.value: Bone marrow with increased numbers of macrophages heavily laden with lipids.

value.value: Monocitosis de la médula ósea

definition.value: Increased count of monocytes in the bone marrow.

value.value: "Catarata ""en girasol"""

Sunflower cataract (SC) is a type of anterior subcapsular cataract almost only seen in Wilson disease, an autosomal-recessive condition with a defect in the metabolism of copper leading to accumulation of copper in the liver and basal ganglia. SC consists of a thin, centralized opacification that is located directly under the anterior capsule and encompasses between one-third and one-half of the anterior lens pole surface area. In all cases, the central opacification is surrounded by additional, secondary opacifications arranged in ray-like structures around it. This pattern is said to resemble a sunflower, with a large central disk surrounded by petals.
Anticuerpos positivos anti-lamina A
The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against lamin A.
Anticuerpos positivos anti-lámina C
The presence of autoantibodies in the blood circulation that react against human lamin C.
Anticuerpos positivos antivinculina
The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against vinculin.
Anticuerpos positivos anti-anexina A5
The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against annexin A5.
Fontanela abultada
An outward curving of a fontanelle, which occurs when fluid builds up in the brain or the brain swells, causing increased pressure inside the skull.
Sindactilia cutánea de los dedos 3-4 de los pies
A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the toes 3 and 4.
Uña triangular
Nail so wide as long with a distal part presenting an acute angle.
Sinostosis tibioperonea distal
Fusion of the distal (i.e.., located away from the trunk) part of the tibia and fibula.
Osificación metacarpiana anormal

Any abnormal process of ossification of the metacarpal bones, which normally are each ossified from two centers: one for the body, and one for the head (metacarpal II,III,IV, and V) and one for the body and one for the base (metacarpal I). At the eighth to ninth week of fetal life, ossification commences in the middle of the body. At the third year the distal extremities of the metacarpals of the fingers and the base of the metacarpal of the thumb begin to ossify; they unite with the bodies at about the twentieth year.
Espolón costal
A bony projection (spur, osteophyte) originating from a rib.
Hueso ilíaco en forma de media luna
Deficient mineralization of the iliac wings, giving a paraglider/crescent shape to the iliac bone.
Osificación anormal del isquion
An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of ischial bones.
Fractura del cuello femoral
A partial or complete breakage of the neck of femur.
Material hialino eosinofílico de la dermis papilar

Accumulation of eosinophilic hyaline material observed around the papillary dermis and the blood vessels located in it. The papillary dermis is the uppermost layer of the dermis. It intertwines with the rete ridges of the epidermis and is composed of fine and loosely arranged collagen fibers.
Neoplasia mucinosa papilar intraductal pancreática

Intraductal papillary mucinous neoplasm (IPMN) is an exocrine neoplasm of the pancreas consisting of epithelial cells growing within the pancreatic ducts (main pancreatic duct or its major branches) and producing mucin. IPMN is a mucin-producing pancreatic cystic tumor. IPMN contains epithelial cells that can create papillary projections.
Vasculitis de vasos medianos

A type of vasculitis (inflammation of blood vessel walls) that affects medium-sized blood vessels. By common usage, vasculitis predominantly refers to arterial disease. Medium-sized vasculitis is observed in diseases including polyarteritis nodosa, Kawasaki disease, and cutaneous polyarteritis nodosa.

label.value: Elevated muscle fiber laminin alpha 5 expression

value.value: Expresión elevada de laminina alfa 5 de fibra muscular

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Elevated muscle fiber laminin alpha 5 expression

value.value: A decreased amount of laminin alpha-5 in muscle tissue. This feature can be shown by immunohistochemistry or Western blotting of muscle tissue. Laminin subunit alpha-5 is a protein encoded by the LAMA5 gene.
Masa paravertebral

A swelling or enlargement localized next to the vertebral column. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.
Flebolito

A calcified structure that forms within a vein. The pathogenesis of phleboliths is thought to involve an organized thrombus produced when the peripheral blood flow slows. The thrombus calcifies, form- ing the core of the phlebolith. Then, the fibrinous com- ponent undergoes secondary calcification and becomes attached. Repetition of this process causes enlargement of the phlebolith.
Ruptura de vejiga

A perforation in the wall of the urinary bladder. Bladder rupture, a relatively rare condition, is most commonly due to abdominal or pelvic trauma but may be spontaneous or iatrogenic in association with surgical or endoscopic procedures. In most cases, patients with bladder rupture have gross hematuria. Other symptoms of bladder rupture include pelvic pain, lower abdominal pain, and difficulty voiding.
Carga elevada de hierro en el miocardio
Increased amount of iron in myocardial tissue.

definition.value: This feature can be assessed by magnetic resonance imaging (MRI). MRI as a reliable, valid, and robust method can provide indirect assessment of cardiac iron overload. Even, it has been advised to determination the degree of cardiac iron overload.8 The reciprocals of T2 and T2*, known as R2 and R2*, are directly proportional to iron. This feature can be seen as a consequence of transfusion treatment in thalassemia.

value.value: Anomalía del movimiento de la pared regional del ventrículo derecho

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Right ventricular regional wall motion abnormality

label.value: Right ventricular regional wall motion abnormality

value.value: The occurrence of abnormal or absent contractility of a region of the heart muscle of the right ventricule. Conventional assessment of RWMA is based on visual interpretation of endocardial excursion and myocardial thickening from the echocardiogram videos.
Acinesia regional del ventrículo derecho
A region of the right ventricle exhibits absent contraction (akinesia) compared to the rest of the ventricle.

definition.value: This finding can be observed in arrhythmogenic right ventricular cardiomyopathy and other diseases.

value.value: Discinesia regional del ventrículo derecho

A region of the right ventricle exhibits abnormal contraction (dyskinesia) compared to the rest of the ventricle, leading to outward bulging or ballooning during contraction or inadequate inward movement.
Aneurisma ventricular derecho
A localized, abnormal dilation or bulging of a portion of the right ventricular wall.

definition.value: Right ventricular aneurysm can be observed following myocardial infarction, trauma, or infections and with certain congenital heart defects.

value.value: Depósito de inmunocomplejos glomerulares

Accumulation of immune deposits, containing immunoglobulins, complement, and other proteins, at various intraglomerular locations. This can lead to glomerulonephritis, with the type of injury that results being dependent on four factors: the mechanism of the deposit formation, the site of deposit formation, the composition of the deposits and the amount of the deposits.
Depósito glomerular de inmunocomplejo PLA2R
Accumulation of immune deposits, containing auto-antibodies against the podocyte antigen M-type phospholipase A2 receptor (PLA2R) in intraglomerular locations.

definition.value: This feature is seen in the majority of cases of primary membranous nephropathy.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de L-glicerato en orina
The amount of L-glycerate in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
Mixoma mamario

A rare, benign mesenchymal tumor of the breast characterized histologically by stellate, round, and spindle-shaped cells with vesicular nuclei and scant cytoplasm that are scattered in the myxoid stroma.
Cistadenoma de ovario

A common, benign ovarian tumor that carries a good prognosis. The two most frequent types of cystadenomas are serous and mucinous cystadenomas whereas endometrioid and clear cell cystadenomas are rare.
Concentración anormal de ácido N-acetilaspártico en el líquido cefalorraquídeo

definition.value: Any deviation from the normal concentration of N-acetylaspartic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).
Butanone, also known as aethylmethylketon or methyl acetone, belongs to the class of organic compounds known as ketones.

value.value: Disminución de la concentración de ácido N-acetilaspártico en el líquido cefalorraquídeo

definition.value: Concentration of N-acetylaspartic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de mevalonato lactona en orina
The amount of mevalonate lactone in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: This finding has been observed in squalene synthase deficiency.

value.value: Anticuerpos positivos contra el factor von Willebrand
The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react to von Willebrand factor (VWF).

definition.value: This feature is usually seen in the context of Von Willebrand disease (VWD), the most common inherited bleeding disorder. VWD is caused by deficiency or dysfunction of the multimeric glycoprotein, von Willebrand factor (VWF), and is clinically characterized by excessive mucocutaneous bleeding as well as musculoskeletal bleeding in type 3 VWD, the most severe form. Treatment options include infusion of concentrates of VWF, which in some patients leads to the production of alloantikbodies.

value.value: Recuento elevado de células asesinas naturales

definition.value: The count of natural killer cells per volume of blood is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Anticuerpos positivos específicos de miositis

The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that display a high degree of specificity for idiopathic inflammatory myopathy (myositis-specific autoantibodies (MSAs)). MSAs are clinically useful biomarkers to help the diagnosis of polymyositis/dermatomyositis (PM/DM). Many of these are also associated with a unique clinical subset of PM/DM, making them useful in predicting and monitoring certain clinical manifestations.
Osmolalidad sérica anormal

Any deviation from the normal range of the serum osmolality, defined as the sum of the osmolalities of every single dissolved particle in the blood such as sodium and associated anions, potassium, glucose, and urea.
